==Description== 
A '''shyster''' is someone who acts in a disreputable, unethical or unscrupulous way, especially in the practice of law and politics, or a [[con artist]]. 

==Etymology== 
*The origin is mostly likely from German ''Scheisser'' - "incompetent worthless person," literally "defecator".[http://www.webster.com/dictionary/shyster] 

* Other possible origins include a real 19th-century New York Jewish lawyer named Scheuster{{fact}}, [[Shylock (Shakespeare)|Shylock]] a character in [[Shakespeare]]'s [[The Merchant of Venice]]. 
One theory attributes the origin to the carnival game "Coconut Shy," given the reputation carnival workers and their games have{{fact}}. 

==Common Misspellings==
Shyster is commonly misspelled.  Common variants include schister, scheister, sheister, schyster, shister, shiester and schiester.

==Other Uses== 
* It may also be applied as a derogatory term for a [[Hyster]] Fork Truck. 

* This term has been used in [[Isaac Asimov]]'s short science-fiction robot story "Evidence". An atmosphere is created around a falsity and then proven wrong. 

* ([[military]]) '''SS-3 Shyster''' is the [[NATO reporting name]] for the [[R-5]] [[theatre ballistic missile]].

